\citation{Thapa2020}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces The three streams in PhasePhyto. The PC stream takes the grayscale image, runs it through a fixed log-Gabor filter bank with four scales and eight orientations, and encodes the resulting structural maps with a small CNN. The semantic stream feeds the RGB image into a pretrained ViT-B/16 and produces 197 patch tokens of dimension 768. The illumination stream applies CLAHE normalization and a shallow CNN. PC tokens query ViT patch tokens through eight head cross attention. The fused output is concatenated with the illumination embedding before the classifier head. The PC filter bank has no trainable parameters; everything else is learned.}}{3}{}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:architecture}{{1}{3}{}{figure.1}{}}
